article.headline: Liberty 38, Virginia Military 32
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Rashad Jennings ran for 111 yards and one touchdown to lead Liberty to a 38-32 win over VMI on Saturday, handing the Keydets their tenth loss the season. Jennings scored once in the first quarter off a 2-yard run, putting the Flames (6-5, 2-2 Big South) ahead early. A 31-yard field goal from Barrett Way put VMI (1-10, 0-4) in the game with 8:03 left in the second. Wynton Jackson and Pierre Penn answered with a pair of TDs, and Liberty led 24-9 at the half. Sean Mizzer had back-to-back touchdowns in the third quarter on 12- and 1-yard runs, putting the Keydets within one possession. Dominic Bolden held the Keydets off with a 97-yard kick off return late in the third quarter. A 43-yard field goal with just under three minutes on the clock couldn't save VMI. Brock Smith was 8-for-12 with 127 yards and one touchdown for the Flames. Kyle Hughes was 3-for-6 with 57 yards and one touchdown for VMI.
